cs.FL, cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.LO, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with regular languages and their properties. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper involves combinatorial properties of regular languages. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility as the paper discusses bounds on the complexity of regular languages. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possibility as the paper involves the study of regular languages and their properties using logical methods. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper discusses upper bounds on the number of atoms of a language and on the quotient complexities of atoms.
